One Q:

How does anonymity fit with Corporate Transparency Act which requires reporting of beneficial owners (ppl who control DAO or own 25%) to FinCEN? Act only requires 'multiple persons' making decisions for the DAO to be 'decentralized'. If only 2-3 ppl are making decisions, would almost certainly have to report

Also how important is anonymity? As long as you're not exercising 'substantial control' you won't have to report to FinCEN and can remain anonymous. But if you are, or if you own at least 25%, you probably will have to report. Does this matter?

Yeah it seems hard to avoid at this point. It's interesting that ultra-conservative Utah is trying to preserve anonymity, and it does seem like the more decentralized a DAO is, the more likely you can remain anon.
